<p>I&#8217;m asking because I have no interest in a &#8220;dedicated&#8221; SMS application like the stock messaging app. I&#8217;ve been using Contacts+ (Contapps) for a couple years now, and I&#8217;m so entrenched that I just can&#8217;t see how you keep contacts, messaging, dialer, and call log separate. On my phone it&#8217;s just one app. I see these screenshots where the dock has phone, contacts, AND messaging and I just laugh. For me that&#8217;s one button, and I can use the other slots for other, really separated apps. Like camera, or Poweramp. Consolidation of related services, especially when no &#8220;single service&#8221; app looks better, is just smart—and I&#8217;d love to see CyanogenMod release their own &#8220;Communications Centre&#8221; like Contacts+ is.</p>
<p>So if this will work with whatever text messaging app I use (in my case Contacts+), I think it&#8217;s awesome. If not&#8230; Well, I don&#8217;t really need secure messaging, but it&#8217;s still awesome because I know a lot of people do (or at least want it).</p>
